lead_paragraph: There is no risk of canceling the Olympic Games in Rio de Janeiro this year due to an outbreak of the Zika virus in Brazil, which has been linked to birth defects in newborns, President Dilma Rousseff's chief of staff said on Monday.

headline.print_headline: Brazil Government Sees No Risk of Canceling Olympics Due to Zika
